com.vernalis.pdbconnector.config

Class XmlDataParsingException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • com.vernalis.pdbconnector.config.XmlDataParsingException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class XmlDataParsingException
extends java.lang.Exception
    This class is used to record any errors generated during XML parsing. As the datacell generated is still required to be returned by the method, this exception stores both the cell and any messages. Errors can be stored at two levels, enumerated in XmlDataParsingException.Level

    The value of the stored data cell must be set with a call to setCell(DataCell), as it's value may not be known at exception time

    Author:
    S.Roughley
